DurationFormatUtils returns wrong result
DurationFormatUtils returns wrong result.  oddly, it is only when Date is set to Dec 31, 2005 The following code will result in a String of -2 which is way off. I've tested against 2.1 and 2.2.         Calendar cal = Calendar.getInstance();         cal.set(Calendar.MONTH, Calendar.DECEMBER);         cal.set(Calendar.DAY_OF_MONTH, 31);         cal.set(Calendar.YEAR, 2005);         cal.set(Calendar.HOUR_OF_DAY, 0);         cal.set(Calendar.MINUTE, 0);         cal.set(Calendar.SECOND, 0);         cal.set(Calendar.MILLISECOND, 0);         String result = DurationFormatUtils.formatPeriod(cal.getTimeInMillis(), System.currentTimeMillis(), "MM");         System.out.println(result);